					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">SkinnyV wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think you just connect the pin labeled LED to anode and the cathode to ground.</div><br /><br />Yeah, and if you want the opposite indication (on during normal operation), you would connect the anode to 5V and the cathode to the LED pin.<br /><br />But don't forget the current limiting resistor, else the diode will be emitting smoke instead of light. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

