					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I thought the &quot;bad sport games&quot; phenomenon started in the fourth generation (Genesis and Super NES) when the leagues and players' associations started to warm up to licensing annual rosters for official video game adaptations. Prior to that, sport games like <em>Blades of Steel</em> and <em>Tecmo Bowl</em> had to stand on their own gameplay merits as opposed to relying on being published by the only publisher to have negotiated the license.</div>

